text: Rubus ellipticus, the golden evergreen raspberry or golden Himalayan raspberry, is commonly known as Ainselu. It is a species of thorny fruiting shrub in the rose family. It is native to the Indian subcontinent. It is also found in southern China, Indochina and the Philippines. == References == ellipticus Category:Plants of Indo-China Category:Plants of Pakistan
